{"type":"text","timestamp":1777776279158,"sessionID":"ses_2144c4c68ffe7cXSNq7AA0JC8F","part":{"id":"prt_debb93106001GJVtwEaRNKnr0n","messageID":"msg_debb929ba0013PPSi94dOhbysx","sessionID":"ses_2144c4c68ffe7cXSNq7AA0JC8F","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-001-r10s0.yaml`.\n\n**Summary**: Pipeline only MULH/MULHU/MULHSU (cold in CoreMark) via a registered tap on the shared DSP's high-32 output, keeping MUL (hot) combinational. This combines r5s1's cold-op sequentialization pattern with r7s1's warning that MUL is hot, using the fact that the 33×33 signed multiplier's high-32 carry chain is the widest arithmetic tree in EX. The implementation mirrors divider.sv scaffolding (ALTOPS gate, hazard_unit OR-in, alu_result_eff mux extension) — no pipeline payload widening (r5s2 trap avoided), no CSE of LUT4 adders (r7s0 trap avoided), and module-scoped rewrite only (r9s0/r9s1 pipelined-operand trap avoided).","time":{"start":1777776275718,"end":1777776279157}}}
