{"type":"text","timestamp":1777777245624,"sessionID":"ses_2143b044dffeQynofhidL0JK7r","part":{"id":"prt_debc7f1c0001GVifEnCiuotudI","messageID":"msg_debc7e52e001qhmDRURdobauxJ","sessionID":"ses_2143b044dffeQynofhidL0JK7r","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-001-r11s0.yaml`.\n\n**Summary:**\n- **Category:** micro_opt (algebraic simplification, r8s0 pattern)\n- **Target:** `ex_stage.sv` — the `div_busy` expression driving `hazard_unit`'s four stall/hold outputs\n- **Key insight:** `div_busy = X && (div_busy_int || (X && !div_busy_int))` reduces to `div_busy = X` where `X = is_div_op && in.valid && !div_done_int`. The `|| div_start_pulse` term is algebraically redundant against the outer AND.\n- **Why this isn't the r9s2 trap:** hazard_unit's stall outputs are OR-reductions, not priority muxes, so Yosys's priority-mux absorption doesn't already cover this. It's a genuine LUT4-level reduction.\n- **Why this isn't the r9s0 trap:** No reliance on pipelined-operand invariants (no `in.pc[1:0]=0` or `rs1` assumptions) — pure boolean algebra over signals driven within ex_stage itself.\n- **Expected impact:** +2%, medium confidence. Worst case: no-op if Yosys already found it.","time":{"start":1777777242560,"end":1777777245622}}}
