it off EX critical path\"\nfitness_delta_pct\": 15\nfitness_delta_pct\": 15\noutcome\": \"regression\"\ntitle\": \"BTB with 1-bit hysteresis for taken branches and unconditional jumps\"\noutcome (taken & target) against the prediction carried with the\\ninstruction:\\n  - correctly-predicted tak\noutcome\\n(write port driven from EX). JAL writes its immediate target.\\nJALR updates the stored target each\nfitness_delta_pct\": 12\noutcome.\"}\noutcome on every branch/jump.\"}\nfitness_delta_pct\": 12\noutcome.\"}\noutcome on every branch/jump.\"}\noutcome\": \"broken\"\ntitle\": \"Pre-register rd_wdata at MEM/WB boundary to shorten forward + regfile read paths\"\nfitness_delta_pct\": 4\nfitness_delta_pct\": 4\noutcome\": \"broken\"\ntitle\": \"Zero-bubble JAL via IF-stage early redirect\"\nfitness_delta_pct\": 5\nfitness_delta_pct\": 5\noutcome\": \"broken\"\ntitle\": \"Stateless IF-stage static JAL-taken prediction (zero bubble on unconditional jumps)\"\nfitness_delta_pct\": 3\nfitness_delta_pct\": 3\noutcome\": \"improvement\"\n","exit":0,"description":"Grep detailed outcomes","truncated":false},"title":"Grep detailed outcomes","time":{"start":1777768229974,"end":1777768229976}},"metadata":{"openrouter":{"reasoning_details":[{"type":"reasoning.text","text":" I'm recalling previous attempts at optimizing divider and multiplier timing—there was an iterative shift-subtract approach and a multi-cycle M-extension unit, but both ended up off the critical path or caused regressions. Let me dig into what actually happened with those implementations.","format":"anthropic-claude-v1","index":0,"signature":""}]}},"id":"prt_deb3e6bcd001Ws58eGg95FuWZh","sessionID":"ses_214c24e41ffeOiI2kB73OyuQJU","messageID":"msg_deb3e5ec6001CJHUdMyqM8dSO8"}}
