{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777769743484,"sessionID":"ses_214ac9d96ffe0M9pTsTF9eWR2u","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_bdrk_01GCWNEaV8i1QwGoVFb5E1oP","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-001-r4s0.yaml","content":"id: hyp-20260502-001-r4s0\ntitle: \"Unified EX-stage subtractor: share ALU SUB/SLT/SLTU and branch comparator\"\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The EX stage currently contains two parallel comparator networks that\n  consume the same post-forward rs1/rs2 operands:\n\n    1. ALU ops SUB / SLT / SLTU — each compiled separately via `a - b`,\n       `$signed(a) < $signed(b)`, and `a < b` in alu.sv's case arms.\n    2. Branch resolve in ex_stage.sv — six funct3-indexed compares\n       (BEQ/BNE/BLT/BGE/BLTU/BGEU), structurally independent of the\n       ALU.\n\n  That is two full-width adder/subtractor trees plus two equality trees\n  competing for LUT4s and fanout on the forward-mux outputs. Yosys CSE\n  does fold some of this, but the compares live in two different\n  `always_comb` blocks in two different modules with different output\n  polarities (signed/unsigned/equal/not-equal) so the sharing is far\n  from guaranteed on GW2A.\n\n  The r3s0 win (+8.50%) proved that on Tang Nano 20K the EX path is\n  area/routing-bound rather than timing-bound: explicitly collapsing\n  three redundant DSP multipliers into one paid off even though each\n  sub-expression was already single-cycle. The same structural\n  consolidation opportunity exists here for the 32-bit sub/compare\n  logic — a fifth of EX-stage LUTs in a typical textbook 5-stage go\n  to these parallel comparators.\n\nhypothesis: |\n  Introduce a single shared 33-bit signed subtract at the front of the\n  EX stage:\n\n      logic [32:0] sub_a_ext = {rs1[31], rs1};   // sign-extend for signed\n      logic [32:0] sub_b_ext = {rs2[31], rs2};\n      logic [32:0] sub_s33   = $signed(sub_a_ext) - $signed(sub_b_ext);\n      logic [33:0] sub_u34   = {1'b0, rs1} - {1'b0, rs2};   // borrow bit\n\n  From this one subtractor derive the shared flags:\n\n      lt_signed   = sub_s33[32];     // MSB of signed 33-bit difference\n      lt_unsigned = sub_u34[32];     // borrow-out of unsigned subtract\n      is_zero     = (sub_s33[31:0] == 32'b0);\n\n  Drive the branch comparator in ex_stage.sv from {is_zero, lt_signed,\n  lt_unsigned} via a 6-way funct3 mux — identical semantics to the\n  current `$signed(rs1) < $signed(rs2)` etc. arms, but sourced from\n  one subtractor instead of six.\n\n  In alu.sv, reshape SUB/SLT/SLTU to consume the same a/b inputs via\n  an equivalent single-subtract structure:\n\n      ALU_SUB:  out = sub_s33[31:0];\n      ALU_SLT:  out = {31'b0, sub_s33[32]};\n      ALU_SLTU: out = {31'b0, sub_u34[32]};\n\n  Because the ALU's a/b differ from ex_stage's rs1/rs2 for I-type\n  SLTI/SLTIU (alu_src selects immediate), keep the ALU's copy operating\n  on alu_a/alu_b, and the ex_stage branch compare on rs1/rs2. The two\n  subtractors have IDENTICAL structure but distinct operand sources, so\n  Yosys will emit two adder chains not one — but each replaces\n  three/six separate compare paths, for a net reduction of about 4\n  comparator trees worth of LUT4s in the EX stage.\n\n  For BRANCH instructions specifically (ctrl.alu_src=0, ctrl.is_auipc=0),\n  alu_a==rs1 and alu_b==rs2, so the ALU-internal subtractor and the\n  ex_stage branch subtractor are bit-identical on that cycle. Yosys's\n  resource-sharing pass (share -aggressive) should fold these two into\n  one physical subtractor when it observes they share the same inputs\n  under mutually-exclusive enable signatures, which is common-case for\n  in-order pipelines.\n\n  Correctness: RV32I semantics unchanged — signed LT from the 33-bit\n  sign-extended subtract's MSB is textbook, unsigned LT from borrow-out\n  is textbook, equality from zero-check on the 32-bit difference is\n  textbook. `a - b` for SUB is the low 32 bits of sub_s33. No change to\n  RVFI taps, pipeline payload, or stage depth. Decoder and regfile\n  unchanged. The ALTOPS M-ext branch in alu.sv and all M-ext paths\n  remain untouched (MUL/DIV remain on their existing hardware).\n\n  Expected fitness path: ~4-5% LUT4 reduction in ex_stage + alu\n  combined, freeing nextpnr routing slack. Same-day P&R seeds typically\n  convert 3-4% LUT reduction into ~1-3% Fmax on Tang Nano 20K's\n  congested-floorplan regime, which directly multiplies into fitness\n  since IPC is unchanged.\n\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n  confidence: medium\n\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n    description: \"Introduce a shared 33-bit signed subtract + 34-bit unsigned subtract at the top of the combinational block; drive ALU_SUB from sub_s33[31:0], ALU_SLT from sub_s33[32], ALU_SLTU from sub_u34[32]. Rest of ALU case arms unchanged. Keep MUL consolidation from r3s0 intact.\"\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: \"Replace the six-way funct3 case with a single 33-bit signed subtract + 34-bit unsigned subtract at the top of the EX combinational block; derive lt_signed / lt_unsigned / is_zero flags, then drive branch_cond via a small funct3 mux over {is_zero, lt_signed, lt_unsigned}. branch_taken / branch_target / redirect logic downstream unchanged.\"\n  - file: test/test_pipeline.py\n    description: \"Add a regression vector that exercises each BRANCH funct3 (BEQ/BNE/BLT/BGE/BLTU/BGEU) against the boundary operands 0/0, INT_MIN/INT_MAX, and -1/0 to confirm the shared subtractor's sign/zero flags match the original per-arm compares.\"\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-001-r4s0.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-001-r4s0.yaml","time":{"start":1777769743469,"end":1777769743482}},"metadata":{"openrouter":{"reasoning_details":[{"type":"reasoning.text","text":" The hypotheses directory is empty, so I need to write one out. My idea is to consolidate the 33-bit subtraction logic used in both the ALU (for SUB, SLT, SLTU instructions) and the branch comparator (for BEQ, BNE, BLT, BGE, BLTU, BGEU), similar to how the DSP consolidation eliminated redundant arithmetic operations in the r3s0 design.\n\nWriting the YAML...","format":"anthropic-claude-v1","index":0,"signature":""}]}},"id":"prt_deb552375001ZH7qO9wr2daGXk","sessionID":"ses_214ac9d96ffe0M9pTsTF9eWR2u","messageID":"msg_deb551421001JTxy75N63zFwEQ"}}
