{"type":"text","timestamp":1777769750175,"sessionID":"ses_214ac9d96ffe0M9pTsTF9eWR2u","part":{"id":"prt_deb558e320015ZNTK0tZIdtFGQ","messageID":"msg_deb5584c1001wX9hynwU2p31U7","sessionID":"ses_214ac9d96ffe0M9pTsTF9eWR2u","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-001-r4s0.yaml`.\n\n**Summary**: `micro_opt` in the spirit of r3s0's +8.50% DSP consolidation win — collapse redundant EX-stage comparator arithmetic into shared subtractors.\n\n- Replace six independent funct3-indexed branch comparators (BEQ/BNE/BLT/BGE/BLTU/BGEU) with a single 33-bit signed subtract + 34-bit unsigned subtract, deriving `{is_zero, lt_signed, lt_unsigned}` flags.\n- Mirror the same shape inside `alu.sv` for SUB/SLT/SLTU so Yosys's resource-sharing pass can physically fold the ex_stage and alu subtractors on BRANCH cycles (when alu_src=0 the operand sources are identical).\n- No pipeline-payload changes, no RVFI tap changes, no new formal state — sidesteps the predictor-class failures of r3s1/r3s2.\n- Expected: +3%, medium confidence. Mechanism is LUT4 reduction → nextpnr routing slack → Fmax, mirroring the r3s0 area-bound regime on Tang Nano 20K.","time":{"start":1777769745970,"end":1777769750172}}}
