{"type":"text","timestamp":1777771827793,"sessionID":"ses_2148d60e7ffeY8NESW3ewx766W","part":{"id":"prt_deb7549140013zmpOrTcVxt90L","messageID":"msg_deb754247001Oa6DsQ0X3uFw85","sessionID":"ses_2148d60e7ffeY8NESW3ewx766W","type":"text","text":"Wrote the hypothesis to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-001-r6s0.yaml`.\n\n**Summary**: Structural consolidation of the three independent 32-bit barrel shifters (SLL/SRL/SRA) in `alu.sv` onto a single shared right-shifter using bit-reversal for SLL and a fill-bit mux (0 for SRL, a[31] for SRA).\n\n**Rationale**: Directly mirrors the r3s0 pattern (+8.50%: fold three MUL DSPs into one) — the proven winning play on this area/routing-bound Tang Nano 20K fabric. Three independent 32-bit variable barrel shifters cost ~240 LUT4 but only one result is selected per cycle; Yosys CSE doesn't fold them because directions and fill disciplines differ. Purely combinational, identical bit-level semantics (formal-invariant), zero IPC impact. Single-file change.","time":{"start":1777771825428,"end":1777771827793}}}
