{"type":"text","timestamp":1777776135966,"sessionID":"ses_2144c4cddffeIMXcJtvP00ok4P","part":{"id":"prt_debb6fd6600106e853xXZcaPIm","messageID":"msg_debb6f79f001y2bEy56PsoGNL1","sessionID":"ses_2144c4cddffeIMXcJtvP00ok4P","type":"text","text":"I've written the hypothesis to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-002-r10s1.yaml`.\n\n**Summary of the pitch:**\n- **Category:** structural\n- **Target:** the remaining load-use bubble — the biggest untapped IPC angle after branch-prediction saturation\n- **Approach:** add a fourth forwarding source in `forward_unit` sourced from `mem_stage`'s *pre-flop* `load_data_comb`, gated by a `load_fwd_ok` signal that uses the **exact same** `mem_misalign` expression that already suppresses `ctrl_with_trap.reg_write` inside `mem_stage` — eliminating r8s1's trap-gate mismatch class of bug by sharing the actual wire rather than recomputing the predicate\n- **Key divergence from r8s1:** the `!mem_misalign` gate is literally the same SV signal in both the forward-point and the reg_write-suppression path (same instance inside mem_stage, exposed to the outside), so there's no chance of a formula drift that could cause `reg_ch0` PREUNSAT\n- **Risk:** adds ~3–4 LUT4 levels upstream of the ALU; with 177 MHz Fmax vs 135 MHz target there's headroom, but Fmax may drop ~10–20 MHz. Expected net: +5% fitness from IPC, medium confidence","time":{"start":1777776131430,"end":1777776135963}}}
