{"type":"text","timestamp":1777769980436,"sessionID":"ses_214ac9e5cffeU2A2fUH6dUGm1x","part":{"id":"prt_deb590870003JnttWIaoy7A4ii","messageID":"msg_deb58f8550015yAvhRkE2ip25B","sessionID":"ses_214ac9e5cffeU2A2fUH6dUGm1x","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-002-r4s1.yaml`.\n\n**Summary of the proposal (structural):**\n\nConvert the 5-stage pipeline into a 6-stage pipeline by inserting an IFD register after pre-decode in IF:\n\n- **IF stage** now does: fetch + decode + imm_gen + JAL predict (combinational)\n- **New IFD register** captures `{pc, instr, ctrl, imm, rs1_addr, rs2_addr, rd, valid}`\n- **ID stage** shrinks to just regfile read + id_ex_reg build\n- **EX/MEM/WB** unchanged; RVFI taps unchanged\n\n**Why this is the most promising structural angle:**\n- Fmax is the dominant fitness lever in this workload (every winner gained Fmax)\n- EX-path optimizations (r1s0 divider, r3s0 DSP fold) have already been fully mined; r1s0/r1s1 proved the divider isn't the critical path\n- The remaining deepest combinational window is `BRAM_out → imem_data → decoder_case + imm_gen + regfile_read → id_ex_reg` — a full cycle of ~10-15 LUT4 levels on GW2A\n- Splitting this across two cycles targets +15-25% Fmax\n- IPC cost is bounded: ~3.6% from taken-branch penalty growing 2→3 cycles (JAL stays zero-bubble via existing IF predictor)\n- Net expected: +10-20% fitness\n\n**Formal-risk mitigation learned from prior rounds:**\n- Unlike r1s2/r3s1/r3s2, zero speculative state is added — IFD just registers committed decode output, so SBY induction over symbolic fetch is unaffected\n- Unlike r2s0, no RVFI-observed `mem_wb_t` field is renamed — every `io_rvfi_*_0` tap stays where it is","time":{"start":1777769973872,"end":1777769980435}}}
