{"type":"text","timestamp":1777771796454,"sessionID":"ses_2148d6144ffedWsXEFRGMrtAUF","part":{"id":"prt_deb74c9170018RCDyFH9KdQywk","messageID":"msg_deb74c3ab001YI20DlDjEQ1Tjq","sessionID":"ses_2148d6144ffedWsXEFRGMrtAUF","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-002-r6s1.yaml`.\n\n**Summary**: Structural consolidation of the three separate SLL/SRL/SRA barrel shifters in `alu.sv` into a single unified bidirectional shifter (33-bit arithmetic right-shift + bit-reversal trick for SLL). Directly follows the winning r3s0 pattern (3-DSP MUL → 1-DSP, +8.5%) and r5s1 pattern (sequentialize cold arithmetic, +8.79%): eliminate parallel EX-stage combinational arithmetic that's never simultaneously needed.\n\n- Target: ~250-400 LUT4 reduction in EX, less routing pressure around the ALU output mux\n- No pipeline payload change, no formal state expansion (avoids r1s2/r3s1/r3s2/r4s1/r5s2 traps)\n- No IPC change — shifts stay single-cycle combinational\n- Test coverage via extended `test_alu.py` vectors (shamt edge cases) before formal/fpga\n- Fitness delta estimate: +4%, medium confidence","time":{"start":1777771792663,"end":1777771796451}}}
