{"type":"text","timestamp":1777772645656,"sessionID":"ses_2147f4787ffeae1bMmbW3taIGK","part":{"id":"prt_deb81c0750019bnVx71vMeYcKZ","messageID":"msg_deb81b7f90025KHhho5GWHbq0y","sessionID":"ses_2147f4787ffeae1bMmbW3taIGK","type":"text","text":"Wrote the hypothesis at `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-002-r7s1.yaml`.\n\n**Summary:** Structural hypothesis — sequentialize MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU into a 2-cycle pipelined FSM (`rtl/multiplier.sv`), mirroring r5s1's divider extraction that netted +8.79%. The 33x33 signed multiplier is still the tallest remaining combinational tree in EX after r5s1 removed the divider from it, and CoreMark's dynamic MUL count is negligible, so the IPC cost of 1 extra stall per MUL is dominated by the Fmax win from letting Yosys map the registered product into the GW2A DSP18's pipeline flop. Formal path is ALTOPS-gated (XOR stand-ins stay combinational) so SBY BMC depth is unchanged. No RVFI payload widening — multiplier state is localized to `ex_stage.sv`, respecting the r5s2 containment lesson. Expected delta: +6% fitness, medium confidence.","time":{"start":1777772642421,"end":1777772645653}}}
