{"type":"text","timestamp":1777763541293,"sessionID":"ses_21509ff27ffednDs1q55nk3GD7","part":{"id":"prt_deaf6d6d6001JnxyW3PfPbAE5Y","messageID":"msg_deaf6d1d9001vlGpCL1b6npsn4","sessionID":"ses_21509ff27ffednDs1q55nk3GD7","type":"text","text":"Wrote hypothesis `hyp-20260502-003-r1s2.yaml` at `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/`.\n\n**Summary:** 32-entry direct-mapped BTB in IF stage with 1-bit taken hysteresis and stored target, updated by EX on every resolved branch/jump. Removes the 2-cycle redirect penalty on correctly-predicted taken branches (dominant in CoreMark's tight loops) while keeping RVFI/mem/ALU contracts untouched — mispredicts fall through the existing EX redirect path at baseline cost. Expected +12% fitness, medium confidence. Main risk is Fmax impact from the IF-stage LUT-RAM lookup + mux; fallback plan is a 1-cycle-pipelined BTB read that still nets a gain.","time":{"start":1777763538646,"end":1777763541290}}}
