{"type":"text","timestamp":1777766470968,"sessionID":"ses_214de2280ffeyGR42V0T2BpcXU","part":{"id":"prt_deb2385ef001yDnvw88vvJpLBx","messageID":"msg_deb237fa1001kjs6CoYH3LmdV5","sessionID":"ses_214de2280ffeyGR42V0T2BpcXU","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-003-r2s2.yaml`.\n\n**Summary:**\n- **Category:** predictor (diversity slot)\n- **Angle:** Stateless static JAL-taken prediction in IF stage\n- **Key insight:** JAL is unconditionally taken with a PC-relative immediate computable directly from instruction bits — prediction is always correct by construction, so no recovery logic or prediction-metadata is needed.\n- **Formal-safety:** Zero new state, zero changes to `if_id_t` / `id_ex_t` / `ex_mem_t` / `mem_wb_t`. Avoids the exact failure mode of r1s2 (BTB formal timeout from threading `predicted`/`pred_target` through pipeline structs).\n- **Mechanism:** IF combinationally detects JAL opcode and uses `pc + jal_imm` as next_pc (EX redirect still wins). EX narrows its redirect condition from `is_jump` → `is_jalr`, since IF already fetched from the correct target for JAL.\n- **Expected:** +2–4% fitness from eliminating 2-cycle redirect bubbles on every dynamically-executed JAL (function call prologues/epilogues in CoreMark).","time":{"start":1777766467055,"end":1777766470966}}}
