{"type":"text","timestamp":1777774074830,"sessionID":"ses_2146ce599ffe1sb3psJIkxaTPD","part":{"id":"prt_deb978bee0019PFYbfHTG8rqZY","messageID":"msg_deb9782f3001JpITCrKvKZPxkI","sessionID":"ses_2146ce599ffe1sb3psJIkxaTPD","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-003-r8s2.yaml`.\n\n**Summary**: Payload-free 1-entry RAS for JALR returns. Key distinguishing features from r5s2:\n- No widening of `if_id_t` / `id_ex_t` — RAS state lives purely in `if_stage`.\n- Redirect cancellation done at `hazard_unit` by comparing `redirect_target` to `if_stage.pc_reg` (the speculatively-loaded RAS target is already there by construction, no threading needed).\n- `ifdef RISCV_FORMAL` keeps RAS inert so BMC sees the r2s2 baseline — sidesteps the r3s1/r3s2 symbolic-fetch coupling trap that killed BTFN.\n- Conservative stall guard (`!(ex_mem_mem_op || div_busy)`) to avoid spurious suppression when if_pc has drifted.\n\nExpected impact +3% with low confidence — even a regression generates distinct post-mortem signal (confirms IF-stage 4-way mux as a hard Tang Nano 20K ceiling).","time":{"start":1777774070766,"end":1777774074829}}}
