{"type":"text","timestamp":1777775460551,"sessionID":"ses_21458b9f9ffe9NXVCVvLDmd70H","part":{"id":"prt_debacb742001uhljFPHrJmawkW","messageID":"msg_debacaf92001hT2mvPM2lRxODu","sessionID":"ses_21458b9f9ffe9NXVCVvLDmd70H","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-003-r9s2.yaml`.\n\n**Summary**: A pure algebraic simplification of the existing JAL predictor's IF-stage gating — following the proven r8s0 pattern (+5.99%) rather than attempting another RAS/BTB/BTFN variant (all regressed). The `!flush && !redirect` conjunction in `is_jal_fetch` and the inner `redirect ? redirect_target` leg in `next_pc` are dead logic, dominated by the outer PC-flop priority mux (redirect wins automatically; stall holds PC on imem_stall). Simplifying shortens the IF combinational critical path by ~1 LUT4 level and may collapse the next_pc mux from 3-way to 2-way. Zero payload widening, zero new state, zero formal-proof impact. Low confidence given the saturation of the predictor slot, but near-zero regression risk.","time":{"start":1777775458114,"end":1777775460550}}}
