{"type":"text","timestamp":1777778020083,"sessionID":"ses_2142fef91ffeS7Emr0lEdRj3ks","part":{"id":"prt_debd3c59b001JPatqlNsX0vW36","messageID":"msg_debd3bf44001HmlzTx6CtcqiKK","sessionID":"ses_2142fef91ffeS7Emr0lEdRj3ks","type":"text","text":"Wrote the hypothesis to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-001-r12s0.yaml`.\n\n**Summary**: Absorb `div_result` into the ALU's DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU case arms, eliminating the external `alu_result_eff` 2:1 mux in ex_stage.sv. Saves ~1 LUT4 level on the EX→flop critical arc (structurally, not via boolean rewrite — threads the r8s0/r3s0 needle while avoiding the payload-widening traps of r5s2/r8s2/r10s2 and the forwarding-cone traps of r10s1/r11s1). No pipeline payload fields added, no IF-mux widening, no formal state growth (ALTOPS branch untouched).","time":{"start":1777778017691,"end":1777778020081}}}
