solved outcome.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Instantiate the BTB. On BTB hit with taken_bit set, override next_pc with the BTB target (still subordinate to EX redirect priority). Emit `predicted` and `pred_target` on the IF/ID bundle.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Plumb `predicted` / `pred_target` from IF/ID through into the ID/EX register (no decode changes \\u2014 purely pass-through metadata).\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Compare resolved (taken, target) against the incoming prediction. Suppress the redirect+flush when the prediction matches; issue redirect+flush on mispredict. Drive BTB update port with resolved outcome on every branch/jump.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"On correctly-predicted taken branch/jump, do not assert flush_if/flush_id \\u2014 the IF stream already followed the predicted path. Mispredicts retain the current flush behavior.\"}, {\"file\": \"test/test_btb.py\", \"description\": \"New cocotb suite: unit tests for BTB lookup, update, tag mismatch, aliasing collisions, and a mini-loop trace asserting zero mispredicts after warmup on a 16-iteration backward-branch loop.\"}, {\"file\": \"test/test_pipeline.py\", \"description\": \"Augment with a fetch-redirect-during-prediction scenario: interleave a branch that aliases another in BTB, confirm rvfi_order stays monotonic and pc_wdata is correct on both mispredict and correct-predict cycles.\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 12, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/btb.sv\", \"description\": \"New module. 32-entry direct-mapped BTB with {valid, tag, target, taken} per entry. Combinational read port for IF; synchronous write port for EX updates.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add `predicted` (and optionally `pred_target`) field to if_id_t and propagate through id_ex_t / ex_mem_t so EX can compare prediction vs. resolved outcome.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Instantiate the BTB. On BTB hit with taken_bit set, override next_pc with the BTB target (still subordinate to EX redirect priority). Emit `predicted` and `pred_target` on the IF/ID bundle.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Plumb `predicted` / `pred_target` from IF/ID through into the ID/EX register (no decode changes \\u2014 purely pass-through metadata).\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Compare resolved (taken, target) against the incoming prediction. Suppress the redirect+flush when the prediction matches; issue redirect+flush on mispredict. Drive BTB update port with resolved outcome on every branch/jump.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"On correctly-predicted taken branch/jump, do not assert flush_if/flush_id \\u2014 the IF stream already followed the predicted path. Mispredicts retain the current flush behavior.\"}, {\"file\": \"test/test_btb.py\", \"description\": \"New cocotb suite: unit tests for BTB lookup, update, tag mismatch, aliasing collisions, and a mini-loop trace asserting zero mispredicts after warmup on a 16-iteration backward-branch loop.\"}, {\"file\": \"test/test_pipeline.py\", \"description\": \"Augment with a fetch-redirect-during-prediction scenario: interleave a branch that aliases another in BTB, confirm rvfi_order stays monotonic and pc_wdata is correct on both mispredict and correct-predict cycles.\"}], \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"formal_failed: timeout\\nrun_all.sh exceeded 1800s wall-clock\\n--- partial output (tail) ---\\ne_0: ##   0:00:00  Skipping step 16..\\nSBY 20:30:07 [insn_xor_ch1] engine_0: ##   0:00:00  Skipping step 14..\\nSBY 20:30:07 [insn_xor_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:00  Skipping step 17..\\nSBY 20:30:07 [insn_xori_ch0] prep: finished (returncode=0)\\nSBY 20:30:07 [insn_xori_ch0] smt2: starting process \\\"cd insn_xori_ch0/model; yosys -ql de