ux to `jump_target`, so the retiring JAL reports `pc_wdata = pc + 4` while the next fetched instruction's `pc_rdata` is the real target, breaking `pc_fwd` / `causal` transitively; any IF-side redirect optimization must either (a) compute pc_wdata from the decoded JAL target independently of the EX redirect gate, or (b) keep the EX redirect asserted (even if IF ignores it) purely for RVFI observability.\"}\n","exit":0,"description":"Search for pc narrowing attempts","truncated":true,"outputPath":"/Users/bonetto/.local/share/opencode/tool-output/tool_debf6dac20019aY2DQKefl2gIa"},"title":"Search for pc narrowing attempts","time":{"start":1777780316868,"end":1777780316872}},"metadata":{"openrouter":{"reasoning_details":[]}},"id":"prt_debf6d89a001T1RNaYdKCByxXO","sessionID":"ses_2140cfe47ffeXzMnBiCl655KRX","messageID":"msg_debf6cb8500176P5TyE3L21M20"}}
