{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777780342630,"sessionID":"ses_2140cfe47ffeXzMnBiCl655KRX","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_bdrk_019DjeSrCC3aBtMiaC3Lnr9e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-001-r14s0.yaml","content":"id: hyp-20260503-001-r14s0\ntitle: \"Narrow IF-stage PC register to 30 bits (pc[31:2]), exploit RV32I pc[1:0]=0 invariant to shorten pc+4 and pc+jal_imm adder carry chains\"\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The IF-stage PC-flop update path is one of the two known-binding Fmax arcs\n  on this Tang Nano 20K flow — r8s0 (+5.99%) won by shortening the\n  pc+jal_imm alignment-guard SELECT, while r8s2/r10s2/r12s2 all regressed\n  by lengthening the predicted-target DATA cone or widening the next_pc\n  mux. The 32-bit `pc+4` and `pc+jal_imm` adders feeding IF's 3-way\n  priority mux still carry their full 32-bit ripple-carry chain even\n  though pc[1:0] is architecturally pinned to 2'b00 by RV32I alignment:\n  (a) RESET_PC=0, (b) pc+4 preserves low bits, (c) is_jal_fetch gate\n  guards instr[21]=0 so jal_target[1:0]=2'b00 when taken, (d) EX's\n  misalign_fault suppresses redirect when redirect_target[1:0]≠0.\n  Synth cannot prove this invariant across the redirect / JAL-predictor\n  feedback loop without help, so it keeps two useless LUT4/carry stages\n  in every IF adder and an unused pair of flops in the PC register.\nhypothesis: |\n  Store the IF-stage PC internally as a 30-bit register pc30\n  (representing pc[31:2]) and expose the full 32-bit value only at the\n  module boundary as `{pc30, 2'b00}` (imem_addr, out.pc). The pc+4\n  adder becomes a 30-bit increment `pc30 + 30'd1`; the pc+jal_imm adder\n  becomes `pc30 + jal_imm[31:2]` with bit [1:0] of the emitted\n  next-pc reconstructed as constant 2'b00 (the is_jal_fetch guard\n  already masks instr[21]≠0, so whenever jal_target actually drives\n  the PC flop its low bits are 2'b00 by invariant). The redirect-write\n  path drops to `pc30 <= redirect_target[31:2]` under EX's\n  misalign_fault gate (redirect=1 implies redirect_target[1:0]=2'b00,\n  since EX suppresses redirect for any misaligned branch/JALR target —\n  this invariant is already exercised by riscv-formal's existing\n  misalign checks). The r8s0 alignment-guard rewrite\n  `(jal_target[1:0]==2'b00) ≡ (imem_data[21]==1'b0)` is preserved\n  unchanged. Expected: ~2 LUT4/carry stages removed from each of the\n  two IF-stage adders + pc_reg shrinks by 2 flops, with zero change\n  to pipeline payload, zero change to RVFI observability (downstream\n  pc is always reconstructed full-width via {pc30, 2'b00}), and zero\n  risk of the r9s0 EX-pipelined-operand trap because the change is\n  strictly confined to if_stage.sv where pc is module-local. Unlike\n  r7s0 (manual CSE of pc+4 regressed due to synth-placement\n  perturbation), this change REMOVES logic rather than adding shared\n  wires — the worst case is synth already doing it implicitly (≈0%),\n  the best case is ~2-4% Fmax via shorter IF-adder carry chains on\n  the binding arc.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n  confidence: low\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: \"Narrow the internal PC register from 32-bit `pc` to 30-bit `pc30` (represents pc[31:2]; implicit pc[1:0]=2'b00 by RV32I invariant). Compute `pc_plus4_30 = pc30 + 30'd1` and `jal_target_30 = pc30 + jal_imm[31:2]` as 30-bit adds. Drive `imem_addr = {pc30, 2'b00}` and `out.pc = {pc30, 2'b00}`. Redirect write: `pc30 <= redirect_target[31:2]` (safe under EX's misalign_fault gate — redirect=1 implies redirect_target[1:0]=2'b00). Non-redirect update: `pc30 <= is_jal_fetch ? jal_target_30 : pc_plus4_30`. Reset: `pc30 <= 30'b0`. The is_jal_fetch guard (imem_data[21]==0 via r8s0 algebraic rewrite), jal_imm formation, redirect priority, and flush/stall priority are unchanged. imem_data consumption is unchanged. No other rtl/ file touched.\"\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-001-r14s0.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-001-r14s0.yaml","time":{"start":1777780342620,"end":1777780342629}},"metadata":{"openrouter":{"reasoning_details":[{"type":"reasoning.text","text":" Now I'll formulate the hypothesis based on this analysis.","format":"anthropic-claude-v1","index":0,"signature":""}]}},"id":"prt_debf6ec2a001h91R4iInjQSloT","sessionID":"ses_2140cfe47ffeXzMnBiCl655KRX","messageID":"msg_debf6db000016Tb5rFRmyHTXKL"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1777780342632,"sessionID":"ses_2140cfe47ffeXzMnBiCl655KRX","part":{"id":"prt_debf6e539001Hx2suk21NH4aVN","messageID":"msg_debf6db000016Tb5rFRmyHTXKL","sessionID":"ses_2140cfe47ffeXzMnBiCl655KRX","type":"text","text":"No prior attempt at narrowing the PC register. This hypothesis follows the r8s0 pattern (+5.99%): module-local arithmetic chain shortening via RV32I invariants, confined to `if_stage.sv`. It strictly *removes* gates rather than adding them, explicitly avoiding the r8s2/r10s2/r12s2 failure mode of widening the IF next_pc path.","time":{"start":1777780319545,"end":1777780342631}}}
