{"type":"text","timestamp":1777780349772,"sessionID":"ses_2140cfe47ffeXzMnBiCl655KRX","part":{"id":"prt_debf745d8001YbGpPv5ZRamdyv","messageID":"msg_debf73faf001mwGBukJV1Ty4BO","sessionID":"ses_2140cfe47ffeXzMnBiCl655KRX","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written. Summary:\n\n**hyp-20260503-001-r14s0** — `micro_opt`: Narrow IF-stage PC register to 30 bits (pc[31:2]), shortening both the `pc+4` and `pc+jal_imm` adders by 2 bits of carry chain.\n\n**Pattern match**: Mirror-image of r8s0's win (+5.99%). r8s0 shortened the SELECT cone of IF's next_pc mux by exploiting RV32I invariants; this shortens the DATA cone by exploiting the same `pc[1:0]=0` invariant — confined to `if_stage.sv` where pc is module-local (r9s0-safe).\n\n**Avoided traps**:\n- Not widening the next_pc mux (r8s2/r10s2/r12s2)\n- Not lengthening the predicted-target DATA cone (r12s2) — shortens it\n- Not crossing a flop boundary (r9s1/r13s2)\n- Not hand-lifting a shared signal into new cross-island wires (r7s0)\n- Not touching EX-stage pipelined operands (r9s0)\n- Not restating a mux/boolean structure (r9s2/r11s0/r12s0/r13s0) — removes register bits\n- No pipeline payload widening (r5s2/r8s2)\n\n**Confidence: low** — synth may already infer this implicitly via propagation, in which case effect is ~0%. But since the change strictly *removes* logic (30-bit reg + 30-bit adders vs 32-bit), worst case is neutral rather than regressing.","time":{"start":1777780344280,"end":1777780349770}}}
