{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777779322402,"sessionID":"ses_2141be1c8ffeUEVAm02sy4gvQG","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_bdrk_017V6HFuRjBLrWAnHZz4XAdn","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-002-r13s1.yaml","content":"id: hyp-20260503-002-r13s1\ntitle: \"Extract EX-stage branch comparator into dedicated branch_cmp module\"\ncategory: structural\nmotivation: |\n  The EX stage currently bundles three structurally distinct combinational\n  cones into one monolithic ex_stage.sv always_comb: (1) the ALU's 19-way\n  case-mux tree (adder/shifter/DSP/SLT/LUI/etc.), (2) the 6-way branch\n  comparator with signed/unsigned subtractor-based less-than, and (3)\n  forwarding muxes feeding both. The branch comparator's signed/unsigned\n  subtractor is structurally orthogonal to the ALU's case-mux tree — it\n  shares no useful subexpressions with the ALU cone under opt_share (the\n  ALU's SLT/SLTU arms use alu_a/alu_b which for BRANCH would be\n  rs1+rs2 via the default ALU_ADD path, not rs1/rs2 directly).\n\n  Per r12s1's converse lesson — \"two smaller modules give nextpnr two\n  independent placement opportunities, one merged module gives it one\n  harder one\" — module-splitting orthogonal cones should help placement\n  on a fabric that is EX-path bound. r3s0 (DSP consolidation, +8.5%) and\n  r5s1 (divider extraction, +8.8%) both won by structurally separating a\n  non-overlapping cone from the main EX flow; this is the same pattern\n  applied to the branch comparator. Unlike r6s0 (barrel-shifter sharing\n  regressed) and r7s0/r11s0 (manual CSE regressed), this change does NOT\n  share or merge anything — it splits an existing monolithic cone into\n  two independently-placeable sub-cones, which matches the direction\n  that has empirically won on this GW2A LUT4 fabric.\nhypothesis: |\n  Extract the branch condition evaluation (BEQ/BNE/BLT/BGE/BLTU/BGEU\n  6-way comparator plus the is_branch gate producing branch_taken) from\n  ex_stage.sv into a new rtl/branch_cmp.sv module with a minimal\n  interface: inputs rs1, rs2 (post-forward 32-bit), branch_op (3-bit),\n  is_branch (1-bit); outputs branch_cond (1-bit) and branch_taken\n  (1-bit). ex_stage.sv instantiates branch_cmp and consumes\n  branch_taken unchanged.\n\n  The branch_target = pc + imm adder STAYS in ex_stage (it shares the\n  pc+4 adder's pc input with other EX arithmetic and moving it would\n  risk the r7s0/r11s0 manual-CSE failure mode). JALR target and\n  misalign-fault detection also stay in ex_stage for the same reason.\n  Only the pure comparator cone — the structurally-distinct signed/\n  unsigned subtractor tree — is extracted.\n\n  Expected mechanism: nextpnr gets an independent placement opportunity\n  for the 6-way comparator cluster, which currently competes with the\n  ALU case-mux tree for routing resources inside the ex_stage flattened\n  always_comb region. On a Tang Nano 20K where the EX path is a known\n  binding constraint (see r10s1 -49% when widening EX, r11s1 -49% when\n  retiming across MEM/WB flop, r12s1 -34% when merging decoders into one\n  cone), splitting an orthogonal sub-cone out should reduce EX region\n  congestion without changing IPC, ALU area, DSP inference, pipeline\n  payload, or formal state.\n\n  No RVFI port changes. No pipeline payload changes. No invariant\n  changes. Only ex_stage.sv loses the 6-arm always_comb branch_cond\n  block; branch_cmp.sv gains it.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n  confidence: low\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/branch_cmp.sv\n    description: \"New module with inputs rs1[31:0], rs2[31:0], branch_op[2:0], is_branch; outputs branch_cond, branch_taken. Contains the 6-way case that currently lives inline in ex_stage.sv (BR_BEQ/BNE/BLT/BGE/BLTU/BGEU) plus the is_branch && branch_cond -> branch_taken gate. Pure combinational, no flops. Verilator lint-clean.\"\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: \"Remove the inline branch_cond 6-way case and branch_taken assignment. Instantiate branch_cmp with the post-forward rs1/rs2, in.ctrl.branch_op, in.ctrl.is_branch, and consume the module's branch_taken output. branch_target = in.pc + in.imm stays inline (pc-adder sharing preserved per r7s0/r11s0 lessons). JALR target, misalign_fault, redirect assignment, and EX/MEM register all remain unchanged.\"\n  - file: test/test_branch_cmp.py\n    description: \"New cocotb unit test for branch_cmp: exercises all 6 branch_op values with representative signed/unsigned boundary cases (0==0, INT_MIN<INT_MAX signed, INT_MIN>INT_MAX unsigned, -1<0 signed, 0xFFFFFFFF>0 unsigned) plus is_branch=0 gating. Verifies branch_taken = is_branch && branch_cond bit-exactly.\"\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-002-r13s1.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-002-r13s1.yaml","time":{"start":1777779322384,"end":1777779322400}},"metadata":{"openrouter":{"reasoning_details":[]}},"id":"prt_debe75ba800101xnvyXSPhngUc","sessionID":"ses_2141be1c8ffeUEVAm02sy4gvQG","messageID":"msg_debe756ae001Ju8T2pHjtJ3TT0"}}
