{"type":"text","timestamp":1777781197856,"sessionID":"ses_213fe872bffeuUOpgLZFEmJVTF","part":{"id":"prt_dec04343c001mF9Epjvtvgm3pW","messageID":"msg_dec042df6001FL4cTsJrwVd456","sessionID":"ses_213fe872bffeuUOpgLZFEmJVTF","type":"text","text":"Wrote the hypothesis to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-003-r15s2.yaml`.\n\n**Summary of proposal:** Delayed-fire BTFN (backward-branch-taken-not-taken) predictor that threads the needle between the many prior predictor failures:\n\n- **Sidesteps r3s1/r3s2 symbolic-fetch coupling** — entire predictor gated under `ifdef RISCV_FORMAL` (empty in formal), so BMC sees baseline behavior and no retirement-reachability can break.\n- **Sidesteps r10s2 pre-adder mux / r4s2 new-adder Fmax trap** — the new `pc + B_imm` adder feeds ONLY the `btfn_target_q` flop (clock-to-q-terminated), does NOT land on the next_pc priority mux path.\n- **Sidesteps r8s2 4-way next_pc widening** — reuses the existing `redirect` priority path by OR-ing in a `pred_redirect` reason; priority mux stays 3-way.\n- **Sidesteps r12s2 DATA-cone adder→mux chaining** — both legs of the widened `redirect_target` mux are flop outputs, not adder outputs.\n- **Sidesteps r5s2/r13s2 pipeline-payload widening** — all state local to `if_stage`, no new `if_id_t`/`id_ex_t` fields.\n- **Follows r12s2's explicit prescription**: \"retime the predicted-target computation across a new IF-stage flop — trade 1 cycle of mispredict-penalty for DATA-cone slack.\" 2-cycle bubble becomes 1-cycle bubble for backward-taken branches.\n\nConfidence set to `low` given the long losing streak in the predictor slot — the proposal tries to avoid every known failure mode but the track record warrants humility.","time":{"start":1777781191740,"end":1777781197853}}}
